<h2 class="es-tab-p">Russian Possessive pronouns </h2>
<p>
Possessive pronouns are words used in place of a noun or another pronoun which indicate ownership. In English, these are pronouns "my", "your", "his", "her" etc.
</p>
<p>
As in English, Russian personal pronouns are devided into three persons, and each personal pronoun has a related possessive pronoun. Moreover, most of them agree in gender, number, and case with the modified noun. 
</p>
<p>
The table below represents the nominative case forms of Russian possessive pronouns.
</p>

<table class="st-table" cellspacing="0" align="center" style="margin: 0 auto;">
