<h2 class="es-tab-p">Demonstrative pronoun этот</h2>

<p>
Demonstrative pronouns are words used to point out a person or an object. The most frequently used demonstrative pronoun is <span class="eg">этот</span>, which can be translated into English as "this" and "that", depending on the context. 
</p>
<p>
Demonstrative pronouns agree in gender, number and case of nouns they modify. 
</p>
<p>
The table below presents the nominative case forms of the pronoun <span class="eg">этот</span>:
