<h2 class="es-tab-p">Particular cases of nominative plural </h2>

<h3 class="es-tab-p-p">Neuter nouns ending in -и in nominative plural </h3>

<p>
A few neuter nouns take the ending -<span class="letter">и</span> in nominative plural. These are nouns <span class="eg">колено</span>, <span class="eg">плечо</span>, <span class="eg">ухо</span>, 
and nouns ending in -<span class="letter">ко</span> in nominative singular.   
</p>


<h3 class="es-tab-p-p">Nouns ending in -ья in nominative plural </h3>
<p>
Some masculine and neuter nouns take the ending -<span class="letter">ья</span> in nominative plural. They are not numerous, but some of them are used very often. 
</p>
<p class="bold">
Masculine nouns:
 </p>
<p> 
<span class="eg">стул</span> <span class="egt">chair</span>, <span class="eg">брат</span> <span class="egt">brother</span>
<span class="eg">муж</span> <span class="egt">husband</span>,
<span class="eg">лист</span> <span class="egt">leaf</span>
and nouns <span class="eg">сын</span> <span class="egt">son</span>, and <span class="eg">друг</span> <span class="egt">friend</span> that undergo a stem change. 
</p>

<p class="ital bold">
Neuter nouns: 
</p>
<p>
дерево, перо, крыло
</p>

<h3 class="es-tab-p-p">Nouns мать and дочь </h3>
<p>
Nouns <span class="eg">мать</span> <span class="egt">mother</span> and <span class="eg">дочь</span> <span class="egt">daughter</span> add the element -<span class="letter">ер</span>- to their stem in plural (not only in nominative, but also in other cases): 
</p>
<p>
мать - матери <br>
дочь - дочери 
</p>

<h3 class="es-tab-p-p">Nouns with different words in nominative singular and plural </h3>
<p>
Nouns <span class="eg">человек</span> <span class="egt">person/human</span> and <span class="eg">ребёнок</span> <span class="egt">child</span> use different words for singular and plural: 
</p>

<p>
человек - люди<br>
ребёнок - дети
</p>


	
